Name: sliceutil
Synopsis: Utilities for converting, manipulating, and iterating over slices

Functions.Name: Append
Functions.Comment: Returns a copy of the given slicified value with the given additional values appended.

Functions.Name: At
Functions.Comment:
Returns the element in the given indexable value at the given index.  If the
index is present, the second return value will be true.  If the index is not
present, or the given input is not indexable, the second return value will be
false.

Functions.Name: Autotype
Functions.Comment: Returns a copy of the given slice with each element's value passed to stringutil.Autotype

Functions.Name: Chunks
Functions.Comment: Divide the given slice into chunks of (at most) a given length

Functions.Name: Compact
Functions.Comment:
Removes all elements from the given interface slice that are "empty", which is
defined as being nil, a nil or zero-length array, chan, map, slice, or string.

The zero values of any other type are not considered empty and will remain in
the return value.

Functions.Name: CompactString
Functions.Comment:
Removes all zero-length strings from the given string slice, returning a new
slice with the values removed.

Functions.Name: Contains
Functions.Comment:
Return whether the given slice contains the given value.  If a comparator is provided, it will
be used to compare the elements.
Functions.Signature: Contains(in interface{}, value interface{}, comparators ...CompareFunc) bool

Functions.Name: ContainsAllStrings
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given string slice contains all of the following strings.

Functions.Name: ContainsAnyString
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given string slice contains any of the following strings.

Functions.Name: ContainsString
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given string slice contains a given string.

Functions.Name: Difference
Functions.Comment: Return the slice that results from removing elements in second from the first.

Functions.Name: Each
Functions.Comment:
Iterate through each element of the given array or slice, calling
iterFn exactly once for each element.  Otherwise, call iterFn one time
with the given input as the argument.

Functions.Name: First
Functions.Comment: Returns the first element from the given slice, array or string; or nil.

Functions.Name: Flatten
Functions.Comment: Returns the given slice as a single-level flattened array.

Functions.Name: Get
Functions.Comment: Returns the nth element from the given slice, array or string; or nil.

Functions.Name: Intersect
Functions.Comment: Return the intersection of two slices.

Functions.Name: IntersectStrings
Functions.Comment: Return the intersection of two string slices.

Functions.Name: Last
Functions.Comment: Returns the last element from the given slice, array or string; or nil.

Functions.Name: Len
Functions.Comment: Returns the length of the given slice, array, or string.

Functions.Name: Map
Functions.Comment: Returns a copy of the given slice with each element modified by the a given function.

Functions.Name: MapString
Functions.Comment:
Returns a copy of the given slice with each element modified by the a given function, then
converted to a string.

Functions.Name: Or
Functions.Comment: Returns the first item that is not the zero value for that value's type.

Functions.Name: OrString
Functions.Comment: Returns the first item that is not a zero-length string.

Functions.Name: Rest
Functions.Comment: Returns the all but the first element from the given slice, array or string; or nil.

Functions.Name: Slice
Functions.Signature: Slice(slice interface{}, from int, to int) []interface{}

Functions.Name: Sliceify
Functions.Comment: Takes some input value and returns it as a slice.

Functions.Name: StringSlice
Functions.Comment: Same as slice, but returns strings.
Functions.Signature: StringSlice(slice interface{}, from int, to int) []string

Functions.Name: Stringify
Functions.Comment:
Converts all elements of the given interface slice to strings using the "%v"
format string via the fmt package.

Functions.Name: TrimSpace
Functions.Comment: Trims the whitespace from each element in the given array.

Functions.Name: Unique
Functions.Comment: Returns a new slice with only unique elements from the given interface included.

Functions.Name: UniqueStrings
Functions.Comment: Returns a new slice with only unique string elements from the given interface included.
